<h1>TOMOYO Linux : Behavior oriented system analyzer and protector.</h1>
<table border="0" summary="What is TOMOYO?">
<tr><td><img src="../tomoyo.png" alt="tomoyo.png" width="115" height="150"></td><td>TOMOYO is a security module which focuses on behavior of a system. A process is created to achieve something. TOMOYO lets each process declare behaviors and resources needed to achieve its purpose (like an immigration officer) and permits only declared behaviors and resources (like an operation watchdog). This approach made it possible for users to understand how a Linux system works. You can use TOMOYO as a system analysis tool as well as an access restriction tool.</td></tr>
</table>

